# Threat Model

Assume:

One agent becomes compromised.

Questions:

Can it call another agent?

Can it steal credentials?

Can it access workflow state?

Can it access memory?

Can it impersonate another service?

Can it move laterally?

Can it call enterprise databases?

Can it access secrets?

Can it call external internet?

The architecture should minimize blast radius.

Compromise of one component should not compromise the platform.

